.TH "pci_epc_raise_irq" 9 "pci_epc_raise_irq" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
pci_epc_raise_irq \- interrupt the host system
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "int" pci_epc_raise_irq
.BI "(struct pci_epc *epc "  ","
.BI "u8 func_no "  ","
.BI "enum pci_epc_irq_type type "  ","
.BI "u16 interrupt_num "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "epc" 12
the EPC device which has to interrupt the host
.IP "func_no" 12
the endpoint function number in the EPC device
.IP "type" 12
specify the type of interrupt; legacy, MSI or MSI-X
.IP "interrupt_num" 12
the MSI or MSI-X interrupt number
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Invoke to raise an legacy, MSI or MSI-X interrupt
